    DatePartitionedDailyAvroSource

    public class DatePartitionedAvroFileSource
extends PartitionedFileSourceBase<Schema,GenericRecord>
    Implementation of Source that reads over date-partitioned Avro data. This source can be regarded as the reader equivalent of TimeBasedAvroWriterPartitioner.

    The class will iterate through all the data folders given by the base directory ConfigurationKeys.SOURCE_FILEBASED_DATA_DIRECTORY and the partitioning type PartitionedFileSourceBase.DATE_PARTITIONED_SOURCE_PARTITION_PATTERN or PartitionedFileSourceBase.DATE_PARTITIONED_SOURCE_PARTITION_GRANULARITY

    For example, if the base directory is set to /my/data/ and daily partitioning is used, then it is assumed that /my/data/daily/[year]/[month]/[day] is present. It will iterate through all the data under these folders starting from the date specified by PartitionedFileSourceBase.DATE_PARTITIONED_SOURCE_MIN_WATERMARK_VALUE until either PartitionedFileSourceBase.DATE_PARTITIONED_SOURCE_MAX_FILES_PER_JOB files have been processed, or until there is no more data to process. For example, if PartitionedFileSourceBase.DATE_PARTITIONED_SOURCE_MIN_WATERMARK_VALUE is set to 2015/01/01, then the job will read from the folder /my/data/daily/2015/01/02/, /my/data/daily/2015/01/03/, /my/data/2015/01/04/ etc. When partitions contain pre/suffixes in the form of /my/data/prefix/[year]/[month]/[day]/suffix, one can refer to them via the PartitionedFileSourceBase.DATE_PARTITIONED_SOURCE_PARTITION_PREFIX and PartitionedFileSourceBase.DATE_PARTITIONED_SOURCE_PARTITION_SUFFIX properties.

    The class will only process data in Avro format.
